                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Last Saturday, reports the article, a black man from Richmond addressed a
                    meeting of blacks in Greenville and endeavored to lure the crowd to the "Radical
                    cause by stating that the Radical Congress had passed a confiscation bill and
                    that the lands in Eastern Virginia were now being parcelled out among the
                    colored people." Apparently, the speech provoked a dispute between Radical and
                    Conservative blacks, after members of the latter group disputed the speaker's
                    assertions.</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
